2500|$|Anton Szandor LaVey in his Satanic Bible (1969) has Leviathan {{representing}} {{the element of}} Water and the direction of west, listing {{it as one of}} the Four Crown Princes of Hell. This association was inspired by the demonic hierarchy from The Book of the Sacred Magic of Abra-Melin <b>the</b> <b>Mage.</b>|$|E
2500|$|Time of the Twins is {{a fantasy}} novel in the Dragonlance series written by Margaret Weis and Tracy Hickman. [...] It is the {{beginning}} of the Dragonlance Legends Trilogy, a series detailing the journey of fictional twins, the warrior Caramon Majere and <b>the</b> <b>mage</b> Raistlin Majere, along with the cleric Crysania. [...] The book details the start of their adventure.|$|E
2500|$|Raistlin's Daughter {{is a myth}} {{about the}} {{daughter}} of <b>the</b> <b>mage,</b> Raistlin. [...] In it, Raistlin and Caramon are at an inn and an Irda woman, incredibly beautiful, is magically afflicted and cursed {{to make love to}} Raistlin. [...] Raistlin is likewise afflicted, and he decides to leave into the snowy weather. [...] While in a cave, the Irda comes to him and they make love, lifting the curse. [...] She magically erases his memory afterwards. [...] The Irda goes back to the inn and has the child, dying in the process. [...] More Irda come and reclaim the child afterward.|$|E
